Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.84,0:00:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close. I almost got killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.22,0:00:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're slacking off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really lost your touch...\NUnacceptable, Yoichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.77,0:00:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.02,0:00:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord... Yoshitsune.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.19,0:00:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you thinking, engaging in\Nsingle combat? That's not your style.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.20,0:00:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, did you really think you\Nhad become a true Genpei warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:00:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what you did during the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.09,0:00:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.80,0:00:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were also brought into\Nthis world! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I won't...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.98,0:01:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not follow your orders anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.82,0:01:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you please, Yoichi. I'll see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.61,0:01:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be more... interesting next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.54,0:01:28.54,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Act 8\NMystery CALL ME"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? I mean... who are all of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.17,0:01:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a man who hates the "Ends."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.05,0:01:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Olminu's master and the leader of\Nthe magician organization, the Octobrists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.05,0:01:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the man tasked\Nwith supporting the Drifters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.51,0:01:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and wiping out the Ends who\Nshould not exist in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.39,0:01:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are one of those Drifters?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abe no Haruakira.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.11,0:01:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abe no Haruakira?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.03,0:02:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean Abe no Seimei?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.16,0:02:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that I've been called "Seimei" according\Nto the customary way of naming notables.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.49,0:02:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not worthy of the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.91,0:02:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. It looks like you\Nsettled things over here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.84,0:02:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see more unfamiliar faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.51,0:02:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen. It's Seimei.\NIt's really him--Seimei, Abe no Seimei.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.85,0:02:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you believe it?! Isn't it great?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.93,0:02:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.02,0:02:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really?\N--Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.60,0:02:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be an Onmyodo practitioner in Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.98,0:02:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are an urbanite from the capital, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do the city folks in Kyoto\Nwear weird clothes like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.45,0:02:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I had these made in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.45,0:02:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you shave your head,\Nsince you are the monk from Onmyoji Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.54,0:02:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry, Haruaki! I am so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.42,0:02:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a dense kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.13,0:02:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Master, don't be sad.\NDon't get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.67,0:02:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to deal with them\Nif you let such trivial matters get to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.55,0:03:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... were you also brought into this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.76,0:03:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...after meeting the strange man\Nin the strange passage?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.97,0:03:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It happened one day out of blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.44,0:03:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the man opened the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.78,0:03:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... and I became a Drifter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.78,0:03:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I realized my task...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.58,0:03:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of looking at stars\Nand playing with familiars,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was sent here to destroy the Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.46,0:03:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh... That giant and the\Nwoman who manipulates fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are called the "End," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They really gave us hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.22,0:03:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I whacked her into the well,\Nand then I head-butted her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.35,0:03:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Wh...?!\N--D-Didn't you kill her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.81,0:03:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:03:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.57,0:04:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have gotten away. She is resilient.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.69,0:04:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have done that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... Why didn't you kill her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.95,0:04:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is of the "End." If you don't kill her...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.08,0:04:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking the head of a woman would be\Nno great feat. It would only bring shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.41,0:04:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her gender is irrelevant!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.04,0:04:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not she is a woman, as long as\Nshe's an End, we absolutely must kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a damn about your rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never take a woman's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.10,0:04:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...pawns to be manipulated\Nby the man in that passage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.90,0:04:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.23,0:04:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We follow our own principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.82,0:04:45.78,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shimazu Toyohisa" "We are humans."\N"We're not pawns."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... So, this is a warrior who\Nnever existed during peaceful times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.21,0:04:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They follow strange principles\Nunder the warrior's code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that may be their weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.59,0:05:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why they were chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.71,0:05:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we must definitely kill the Ends...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...before it's too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...whether they are women or children,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.68,0:05:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,regardless of their background!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.60,0:05:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that old man in the wagon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the honorable Hannibal Barca.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is one of the Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has been stuck in a\Nnear-constant state of dementia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.86,0:05:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been getting worse\Nfor the past several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be because of his age.　
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.08,0:05:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was another Drifter...\NThe honorable Scipio Africanus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a longstanding rivalry\Nwith Scipio in the other world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was relatively clearheaded\Nwhile Scipio was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On our way here, we were attacked by\Nthe Black King's troops several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scipio!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.17,0:06:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under fierce attack and pursued by the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.26,0:06:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we were unable to go back to look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The headquarters sent out a search\Nparty for him, but still no luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.35,0:06:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope he didn't fall into\Nthe hands of the Black King.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.15,0:06:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, Hannibal has been in this condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before this, his only problem\Nwas wetting himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet now he is deteriorating rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is hard to imagine, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.03,0:06:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scipio must be an important existence to him--\Nsomeone who keeps him moving forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.84,0:07:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] I want to go home to Rome!\NI want to take a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.35,0:07:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was separated from them,\NI've been walking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,deeper and deeper into the middle of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.65,0:07:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I followed traces of something being dragged,\Nhoping to find a house nearby, but no luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know my name is Africanus,\Nbut that doesn't mean I like Africa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... Why on earth do I have to go\Nthrough this hell after I saved Rome?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bull crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] Wh-What on earth is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] D-Dog?! Dog man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] What?! What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.23,0:08:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin]\NWait! Wait! Wait! What the--?! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.82,0:08:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you, moron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.20,0:08:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.95,0:08:16.32,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lone fighting fire ball"\N"Seven lives to give my country"\N"If I leave to the sea" "Well"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch my precious plane,\Nyou fuckin' jackass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.16,0:08:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pissed off! A foreigner! You Americans\Nand British are savages! Bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you, moron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are a damn American,\NI'll kick your fuckin' ass, jackass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Say something, you bastard!\N--What an evil-looking barbarian.\NHe must be the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.09,0:08:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Did you hear me, you damn idiot?! Huh?!\N--...who was flying that strange thing over the\Nbattle of the "Northern Wall" or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Don't you have a fuckin' voice?! Damn jackass!\N--Does that mean this man is also a Drifter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no clue what he is talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.23,0:08:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which race is he? His face looks so flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.11,0:08:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I expected from the darn barbarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't even speak the universally common\Nlanguage of the great Roman Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.82,0:08:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What the hell, you dumbass?!\N--He must be from a really undeveloped area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.83,0:09:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Did you lose your fuckin' tongue?!\N--Poor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.29,0:09:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Say something! Foreigner! Hey! You hear me?!\N--Even so, he must know the\Nname of my great motherland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.58,0:09:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rome!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.21,0:09:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roma?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:12.84,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Rome"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:15.34,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Italy"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.93,0:09:17.97,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Axis"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.97,0:09:19.10,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Tripartite Pact"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.10,0:09:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] Aww, I am so happy\Nthat he finally understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.77,0:09:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, as expected of my motherland,\Nthe great Roman Empire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.85,0:09:27.56,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sentimental"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.56,0:09:28.15,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sentimental"\N"In 1944, Italy made peace with the Allies.\NBadoglio Regime declares war on Germany."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a goddamned enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.69,0:09:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.11,0:09:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... are the fuckin' enemy,\Nyou pasta-eating freaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.61,0:09:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that "sky god" went on a rampage again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That god is scary. He is over the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.79,0:09:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] Grr! You damn barbarian!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Apologize to Germany,\Nyou fuckin' jackass!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.83,0:09:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] If you can't speak Latin,\Nyou should just die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.43,0:10:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a cartridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cartridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.81,0:10:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Ya didn't know that, pop?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.10,0:10:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. You're from a different era.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pack the gunpowder,\Ncap the end of the shell with a bullet,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then put the cartridge in the chamber.\NWhen the hammer strikes the primer,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it triggers and fires the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crazy, ya fool?!\NDon't waste your bullets!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.34,0:10:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then, is that... the one\Nthat shot down the giant...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.68,0:10:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing that was firing continuously?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called a Gatling gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If ya turn the crank, you can\Nshoot as much as ya want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.06,0:10:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is a useless long piece of iron now,\Nsince we're out of magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's wrong, pop?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.69,0:10:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Argh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.40,0:10:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I feel foolish about my desperate attempt\Nto make ammunition from black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This device could change everything in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.66,0:11:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could annihilate a massive force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riflemen will no longer use formations\Nand instead scatter to strategic locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.79,0:11:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only cavalry but also spearmen\Nwill no longer be needed in a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.26,0:11:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I... I want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.55,0:11:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what it takes, I want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.05,0:11:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.31,0:11:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already researched gunpowder,\Nthe Gatling gun, and other necessities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.85,0:11:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, as to how they are produced...\NWe showed the gun to many blacksmiths.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is impossible to make it with the\Nexisting metallurgy in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, it is a product\Nfrom the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, I have no idea\Nabout explosive "black powder."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid and the other fellow\Nare excellent marksmen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they don't know how to make\Nthe weapon they are shooting with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As to black powder, we are making it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.88,0:11:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?!\N--Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I expected, you fellows are bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've met some Drifters who\Ncarried various weapons in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.85,0:12:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet your governing principle\Ncould completely change this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, all we need is primer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Primer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hit this part, the end\Nof this bullet, it will explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.36,0:12:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this is not black powder,\Nbut a chemical concoction of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.12,0:12:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been researching it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a scientist.\NCan't you figure that out?! Do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am just an Onmyodo practitioner--a sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.29,0:12:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a field for chemists or alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.47,0:12:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh dear, princess, Saint-Germi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.22,0:12:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess, did you catch cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.97,0:12:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my, how terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.64,0:12:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.14,0:12:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.31,0:12:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello. Are Drifters here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.74,0:13:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a member of the Octobrist Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, October or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.62,0:13:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.74,0:13:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Four-Eyed Boobs called Olminu here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.62,0:13:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true... that you are making "black powder"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.08,0:13:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. All we need now is sulfur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.84,0:13:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already asked Boobienu about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Semu! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.26,0:13:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought the "sulfur."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu contacted headquarters\Nand asked them to bring it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It smells horrible.\NWhat on earth are his plans...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It stinks!\N--It stinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.61,0:13:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. She did as I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boobienu is a good girl.\NI'll rub her breasts for her later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We now have everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dwarves" are next!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:14:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man, Nobunaga... He may be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:05.84,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Octobrists"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.50,0:14:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We may need to put him under surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.71,0:14:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may turn this world upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.72,0:14:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Drifters are living beings.\NThey act according to their own principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have a common goal like the Ends,\Nwho are determined to destroy the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no way of\Npredicting what they may do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the man who created the\NOrte Empire, he is probably a Drifter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a doubt, his initial intention\Nfor the new nation was to save people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.91,0:14:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He created the country to rebuild\Nthe dignity of the starving masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, as a result...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.00,0:14:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...endless war erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.54,0:14:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Drifters are unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or is this something that you anticipated...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.55,0:14:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Murasaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh, it smells good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:14:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.02,0:15:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You freed the Elves,\Nmade black powder... What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.40,0:15:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, we're freeing the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.24,0:15:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will drift from place to place,\Nliberating the tribes under Orte's control.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.57,0:15:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will form an alliance with the countries\Nthat have been fighting against Orte,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.16,0:15:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gradually consume\Nthe empire from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.96,0:15:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will mass-produce black powder,\Ngather soldiers, make firearms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.92,0:15:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and wipe the Orte Empire from this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.34,0:15:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will unite the tribes and\Nestablish a multi-racial federation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.59,0:15:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where each race has the right to self-govern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we'll keep military power and\Nappoint Toyohisa as Commander in Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.43,0:15:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll bring the "warrior code" to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.40,0:15:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't put this idea into practice,\Nwe won't be able to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.61,0:15:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only way that we'll be able\Nto wield enough military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.53,0:15:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no other way to defeat the Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to acquire military,\Nwe must establish our own stratocracies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:15:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will lead to a military usurpation of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.58,0:16:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The right of self-government\Nwill become uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do not underestimate me,\NLord Oda Nobunaga!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.46,0:16:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, it's better than Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:12.34,DefaultB,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better than being destroyed by the Ends...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.34,0:16:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Much, much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He actually learned the\NElven language. What is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you see,\NI am a highly competent person...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.31,0:16:38.20,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Conquering the world through military force"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, in the end, the world\Nwill become an excellent place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.73,0:16:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't discriminate against the "Elves,"\Nthe "Dwarves," and the other races.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.53,0:16:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fair taxes, thriving business, peasants living\Nin comfort, disciplined soldiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.36,0:16:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will establish a utopian nation.\NIt's true... Very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... Why do you want to appoint\NLord Toyohisa as a leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you be the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.46,0:16:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is that... I don't have\Nwhat it takes for that sort of role.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.30,0:16:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought profit and fear\Ncontrolled one's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.93,0:17:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the hearts of men\Ndon't seem to work like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.02,0:17:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.73,0:17:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fifty years of my life\Nwere lived completely in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.40,0:17:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, in my former life, when I was\Nbetrayed and the temple was besieged,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the first person I suspected was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.08,0:17:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my own son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.33,0:17:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet that son died in battle,\Nfollowing me to the grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.71,0:17:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter geezer like that should never be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyohisa doesn't care about\Nloss or gain, fear or intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has what it takes to be a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, he is a fool.\NTherefore, he needs an assistant...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.07,0:17:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really senile? Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.49,0:18:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carthage will fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.37,0:18:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't take any measures,\NCarthage will be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.29,0:18:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mago! Mago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.79,0:18:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a great idea. How about climbing\Nover the Alps and invading Rome?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.34,0:18:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shimazu Toyohisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.67,0:18:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Are you Hasdrubal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.76,0:18:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth are you doing here?!\NWhat happened to Carthage Nova, eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that? Is this another Roman attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.76,0:19:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one who can save Carthage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.02,0:19:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Marcus? Or is it Valerius?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.14,0:19:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, doesn't matter.\NI'll kick both of your asses.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.19,0:19:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you really are senile. Even so,\Nyour eyes are not quite dead yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.74,0:19:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Grandpa, what did you do before you lost it?\N--By the way, Hamilcar, will we eat dinner soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.53,0:19:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have fought a great battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.03,0:19:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh...?! What was that?! Is it the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man has the same eyes as my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.64,0:19:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go free the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.06,0:19:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dwarves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.31,0:19:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Dwarves?!\N--A-Are you kidding me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why those damn Dwarves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.27,0:19:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's right! Why them?!\NWe are not obligated to save them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.94,0:20:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Right!\N--Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.41,0:20:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo, you all don't know about\Nthe feud between Elves and Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.33,0:20:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There has been hostility between us\Nsince the dawn of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.46,0:20:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are like oil and water. We never get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Orte destroyed the countries,\Nthey didn't even try to help us Elves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.05,0:20:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you want us to go save those Dwarves...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.13,0:20:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who don't want to help\Ndon't have to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just gonna go conquering.\NOnly true soldiers should join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.32,0:20:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wa... Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo, just hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.91,0:20:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it! Seriously, don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.08,0:20:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do anything that messes up\Nthe plan! I'm serious. Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.58,0:20:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grrrr, that idiot! He'll ruin everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.88,0:21:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grrrr, you fool! Damn idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now, Shara?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's actually going alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... and the guys from\Nmy village will back him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.06,0:21:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man saved our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.89,0:21:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the previous war with the Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if either the Elves or the Dwarves\Nhad thrown away this grudge,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.11,0:21:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if we had joined our forces\Nand risen up against them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe then, neither us nor them\Nwould have fallen to slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.36,0:21:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... don't want to repeat the mistakes\Nour previous generation made.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.54,0:21:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.17,0:21:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, sir, really are an unstoppable arrow.\NWhat is your objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.34,0:21:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you like Nobunaga,\Nwho wants to change the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.84,0:21:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Their heads.\N--Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waking or sleeping, all a Satsuma warrior\Nthinks about is charging forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you coming with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.56,0:21:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Japanese guy is interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.85,0:22:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We... need to go back to headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to find Scipio and also investigate\Nthe movements of the Drifters and the Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? Sounds rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.24,0:22:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take Olminu with you.\NShe should be of use to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.20,0:22:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.87,0:22:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.04,0:22:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is dinner ready yet, grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.83,0:22:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just ate, grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.34,0:22:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.59,0:22:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a dumbass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.38,0:22:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they don't come on their own,\Nthey don't have to come. They'll be useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.02,0:22:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spread the word to the villages!\NWe're gathering troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.03,0:22:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. Way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.95,0:22:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boobienu, prepare that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.74,0:22:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! Beard man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.49,0:22:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.70,0:22:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ya like it, right? Keep that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.58,0:23:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll also be leaving the Gatling gun here.\NWith no bullets, it ain't worth crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.00,0:23:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ya keep talking about incredible things\Nlike making guns and bullets, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.76,0:23:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you perfect it, pass some on.\NBut I am not expecting anything.
